    <h2>Tips</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Audio conferencing is currently "opt-in". If you don't join the audio conference, you won't hear other
            people and they can't hear you.
        </li>
        <li>Movement is a little choppy right now.</li>
        <li>There is an "immersive AR" mode that is unintentional. Not sure if this will stick around as we haven't
            figured out if it's useful or not
        </li>
        <li>To join the immersive experience, click the "VR" button in the bottom right side of your window. This really
            is only useful on Quest rigth now as it
            simply brings up a full screen view of browser on desktop.
        </li>
        <li>This is designed to be inherently secure, the public space can only be accessed if you are authenticated and
            the private link is a local in memory only
            experience (you may be able to join audio, there are some kinks there that are being worked out)
        </li>
        <li>Bug reports/feature requests/general questions can be sent to <a href="mailto:support@immersiveidea.com">support@immersiveidea.com</a>
